GENIE Grid Backend
==================

Prefer the manifest-aware wrapper:

```
analysis/bin/submit_genie_grid_samples.sh
```

It expands the GENIE rows in `analysis/share/config/sample_matrix.tsv`, writes
per-sample `gevgen` argument files under `analysis/output/grid/genie/args`,
copies `production/genie_grid.sh` to `grid_resources_dir`, and calls
`production/submit_genie.sh`.

The lower-level submitter is still available:

```
production/submit_genie.sh [--prod] NUM_JOBS JOB_NAME ARGS_FILE SPLINES_FILE FLUX_FILE FLUX_HIST_NAME OUTPUT_DIRECTORY GIT_CHECKOUT
```

`SPLINES_FILE` and `FLUX_FILE` are passed to jobsub with `-f`. The output
directory should usually be a persistent or scratch PNFS directory.
